---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does an awning window cost installed in Berwick?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Single awning window installed runs $450–$900 in Berwick, Cranbourne and Narre Warren — depending on size and glazing. Small bathroom awnings (600×600mm) sit at $450–$650. Standard kitchen-over-sink awnings (1200×900mm) at $700–$900. Large awnings 1800mm+ wide at $850–$1,200. Double-glaze adds $300–$400 per window. Includes removal, supply (Trend, Stegbar, AWS, Wideline), install, perimeter seal and architrave patch-back." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Why awning windows for kitchens and bathrooms?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Three reasons. (1) Rain protection — the sash opens outward and hinges at the top, so the open glass acts as a small awning over the opening. You can leave them open in light or moderate rain without water coming in. (2) Privacy without curtains — the sash sits 100–300mm proud of the wall when open, which obscures the line-of-sight from the street. Great for ground-floor bathrooms and toilets. (3) Easy operation over a kitchen sink or vanity — the friction-stay opens the window in one motion with a winder handle, no reaching across to slide a heavy panel. Standard for kitchens, bathrooms, laundries, ensuites, toilets across every Casey suburb." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can an awning window be opened from above a sink?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — the standard mechanism is a winder handle mounted at the bottom of the frame, which you operate from below. You wind the handle clockwise to open, anti-clockwise to close. Modern friction-stays hold the sash at any angle without needing to lock — you can crack it 10° for ventilation or wind it fully open. Sash chains can be added on tall awnings to prevent over-opening. Standard reach from kitchen sink is comfortable with a 600–900mm bench-to-sash-bottom distance." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Awning vs casement vs louvre — which for which room?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Awning (top-hinged outward): rain-protected ventilation, privacy, easy operation. Default for kitchens, bathrooms, laundries. Casement (side-hinged outward): full opening, best raw ventilation per window size. Good for bedrooms, narrow tall openings, or where you want a window that catches a side breeze. Louvre (horizontal slats stacked vertically): maximum airflow, weatherproof when closed, but security and insulation less than awnings or casements. Bathrooms in tropical-style homes, sometimes laundries. For a typical Berwick or Cranbourne wet-room window, awning is right 80% of the time." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are awning windows secure against break-ins?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Reasonable — better than sliders for forced-entry resistance. The friction stay limits the open angle so a person can't squeeze through even when wound fully open. Standard awning lock is a key-lockable handle that engages a mechanical bolt into the head of the frame; premium specs add a second locking point. For ground-floor awnings near the front of the house we recommend the keyed handle as standard. Window screens (insect/security mesh) are available — standard insect mesh $80–$150, stainless security mesh (Crimsafe-equivalent) $250–$450 per window." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do awning windows work with double-glazing?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — double-glazing on awning windows is straightforward and we'd recommend it for any new awning install in Berwick. The slightly heavier IGU (insulated glass unit) sash means specifying a heavier-duty friction stay (10–15% premium on hardware) but the operation is identical. Double-glazed awnings are particularly valuable for bathrooms and laundries where condensation from showering and drying is otherwise the worst in the house. Premium of $300–$400 per window over single-glaze." }
    }
  ]
};
---
<Layout
  title="Awning Windows Berwick | Top-Hinged, Rain-Protected | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Awning window replacement in Berwick, Cranbourne, Narre Warren. Top-hinged outward-open windows for kitchens, bathrooms, laundries. Rain-protected ventilation, AS 2047 compliant, $450–$900 installed."
  canonical="https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/services/awning-windows/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Rain-protected ventilation</span>
      <h1>Awning windows in <span class="accent">Berwick &amp; Casey</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Top-hinged outward-open windows &mdash; the sash itself acts as a
        small awning over the opening, so you can leave them open in light
        rain. Standard for kitchens, bathrooms, laundries, ensuites and
        toilets across every Casey suburb. AS 2047 compliant, key-lockable
        handles, double-glaze available.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free measure</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Why awning windows for wet rooms.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Three things only an awning does well.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Rain-protected ventilation:</strong> Top-hinged means the open sash slopes outward and downward &mdash; rain runs off the outside of the glass rather than into the room. You can leave them cracked open through a typical Berwick winter shower or summer storm without worrying about wet floors.</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy:</strong> The sash sits 100&ndash;300mm proud of the wall when fully open, which breaks the line-of-sight from outside. Great for ground-floor bathrooms, toilets and ensuites where you don&rsquo;t want frosted glass everywhere.</li>
          <li><strong>One-hand operation:</strong> Winder handle at the bottom of the frame &mdash; you turn the handle from below to open or close. No reaching across a kitchen sink to slide a heavy panel.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Standard awning sizes in Berwick stock.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Bathroom / toilet:</strong> 600&times;600mm to 900&times;600mm. $450&ndash;$650.</li>
          <li><strong>Kitchen over sink:</strong> 1200&times;900mm. $700&ndash;$900.</li>
          <li><strong>Laundry over trough:</strong> 900&times;600mm to 1200&times;900mm. $550&ndash;$850.</li>
          <li><strong>Ensuite high vent:</strong> 1200&times;400mm (narrow strip above shower). $500&ndash;$700.</li>
          <li><strong>Bedroom secondary:</strong> 1200&times;600mm or 1500&times;600mm. $600&ndash;$900.</li>
          <li><strong>Living/dining accent:</strong> 1800&times;900mm or larger. $850&ndash;$1,200.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Friction stays &amp; sash limits.</h3>
        <p>
          The friction stay is the arm at each side of the sash that holds
          it at any angle when open. Modern friction stays are stainless
          steel, factory-set for the sash weight, and adjustable in
          tension if the window feels too loose or too tight after a few
          years. Most awnings are limited to open about 45&ndash;60&deg;
          from the closed position; sash chains can be added if you want
          to limit it further (typical for ground-floor bedrooms where
          you want ventilation without a person-sized gap).
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Lock &amp; security.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Standard cam lock:</strong> Integrated in the winder handle. Engages a metal bolt into the frame head when wound to fully closed.</li>
          <li><strong>Key-lockable handle:</strong> Premium upgrade. Same engagement, key-secured. Recommended for ground-floor awnings near the front of the house.</li>
          <li><strong>Two-point lock:</strong> Premium spec on larger awnings &mdash; locks at the top and the bottom for extra rigidity.</li>
          <li><strong>Insect screen:</strong> $80&ndash;$150 per window, fits inside the reveal.</li>
          <li><strong>Security screen:</strong> Stainless mesh (Crimsafe-equivalent) $250&ndash;$450 per window.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Awning + condensation = the wet-room win.</h3>
        <p>
          Bathrooms and laundries are where condensation hits worst in any
          Casey house &mdash; hot water vapour, cold winter morning, single
          pane of glass. Double-glazed awnings lift the cold-side surface
          temperature out of the dew-point range and condensation just
          stops forming. If you have mould on your bathroom or laundry
          architraves, double-glazed awnings + improved exhaust fan is the
          fix.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Where we install awning windows.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-casey/">All City of Casey</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free awning window measure-up.</h2>
        <p>Single bathroom swap-out or a whole wet-room refresh &mdash; both jobs welcome.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
